==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Consumers goods
<hw>Con*sum"er's goods</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Polit. Econ.)</fld>
<def>Economic goods that directly satisfy human wants or desires, such
as food, clothes, pictures, etc.; -- called also <altname>consumption
goods</altname>, or <altname>goods of the first order</altname>, and
opposed to <contr>producer's goods</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consumer's surplus</ent>⟦br⟧
